Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Chop the @olives{30} into small pieces. Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150}, quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all). Pick the @rosemary{1/2} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

When the water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the rosemary and @panko breadcrumbs{25}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch it like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, remove the toasted crumbs to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Pop your #pan{} back on medium high heat and add a drizzle of @olive oil{} (no need to wash). Add the mushrooms, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir fry until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the shallot to the pan with the mushrooms and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add in the garlic, @dried Italian herbs{1/2}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}, stir through and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}, @red wine stock paste{28}, lentils and @water{50%ml} into the shallot pan, bring to the boil, stir to dissolve the stock pot. Simmer until starting to thicken, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the olives, half the plum tomatoes and half the parsley in a #small bowl{} along with the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Season with @pepper{} and stir together.

Add the remaining plum tomatoes to the sauce. Stir together and simmer for a further ~{3-4%minutes}, then taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add the drained pasta and remaining parsley to the sauce and stir to combine. Divide among plates and top with a spoonful of salsa and the rosemary crumb.